{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869162966,"sessionID":"ses_285f34793ffedZA5DeT9533kBe","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0cf197001aWSk9KX86nhZoi","messageID":"msg_d7a0ce580001ksJub9qqOYwJTh","sessionID":"ses_285f34793ffedZA5DeT9533kBe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_cd6b7ee40e854f28bb4e9541","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Agent Runtime sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute tools/files via the Router (data plane).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-028\n10: - **Module**: `sdk-python`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: Building upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n20: 1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)\n21: 2. Execute tools and manage files through the Router (data plane)\n22: 3. Query available tools and their schemas\n23: 4. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Requirements\n28: \n29: ### AR-028-001: AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n30: \n31: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: AR-028-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n34: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n35: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n36: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: AR-028-001-B — Data plane init failure after session create\n39: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n40: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n41: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: AR-028-001-C — Router URL required\n44: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n45: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: AR-028-001-D — Constructor parameters with defaults\n49: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n50: - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n51: - **THEN** it SHALL set `name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ### AR-028-002: Tool Execution\n56: \n57: The system SHALL provide a method to execute tools via the data plane.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: AR-028-002-A — Execute tool with parameters\n60: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n61: - **WHEN** `execute_tool(tool_name=\"calculator\", parameters={\"expression\": \"2+2\"}, timeout=30)` is called\n62: - **THEN** the client SHALL POST to `{base_url}/api/execute` with JSON body `{\"tool_name\": \"calculator\", \"parameters\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}, \"timeout\": \"30s\"}`\n63: - **AND** return the result from the data plane\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: AR-028-002-B — Execute tool timeout\n66: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n67: - **WHEN** `execute_tool(tool_name=\"slow-tool\", parameters={}, timeout=5)` is called\n68: - **AND** the tool takes longer than 5 seconds\n69: - **THEN** the client SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with timeout information\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ### AR-028-003: Tool Discovery\n74: \n75: The system SHALL provide methods to discover available tools and their schemas.\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: AR-028-003-A — List available tools\n78: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n79: - **WHEN** `list_tools()` is called\n80: - **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/tools`\n81: - **AND** return a list of tool names\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: AR-028-003-B — Get tool schema\n84: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n85: - **WHEN** `get_tool_schema(tool_name=\"calculator\")` is called\n86: - **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/tools/calculator/schema`\n87: - **AND** return the tool's input/output schema\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ### AR-028-004: File Operations\n92: \n93: The system SHALL provide file operation methods via the data plane.\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: AR-028-004-A — Upload file\n96: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n97: - **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/tmp/data.csv\", remote_path=\"/data/input.csv\")` is called\n98: - **THEN** the client SHALL POST multipart form data to `{base_url}/api/files` with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n99: - **AND** the file SHALL be available at `/data/input.csv` in the runtime\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: AR-028-004-B — Download file\n102: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n103: - **WHEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/output/result.csv\", local_path=\"/tmp/result.csv\")` is called\n104: - **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/files/output/result.csv` with `stream=True`\n105: - **AND** write the content to `/tmp/result.csv`\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: AR-028-004-C — List files\n108: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n109: - **WHEN** `list_files(path=\"/data\")` is called\n110: - **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/files?path=/data`\n111: - **AND** return a list of files in that directory\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ### AR-028-005: Data Plane Client URL Construction\n116: \n117: The `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL construct the base URL from router components.\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: AR-028-005-A — Base URL from router components\n120: - **GIVEN** `router_url=\"https://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"prod\"`, `cr_name=\"my-agent\"`\n121: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without `base_url`\n122: - **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` as `https://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: AR-028-005-B — Explicit base URL\n125: - **GIVEN** `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"` is explicitly provided\n126: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated\n127: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### AR-028-006: Session Header\n132: \n133: All data plane requests SHALL include the session ID header.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: AR-028-006-A — Session header on requests\n136: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"session-123\"`\n137: - **WHEN** any data plane method is called (e.g., `execute_tool`, `list_tools`)\n138: - **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: session-123`\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## Non-Requirements\n143: \n144: The following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n145: - Code interpretation functionality (covered in AR-027)\n146: - WebSocket connections for streaming (future enhancement)\n147: - Authentication beyond JWT token (handled by ControlPlaneClient)\n148: - Tool implementation (provided by runtime)\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Dependencies\n153: \n154: | Dependency | Description |\n155: |------------|-------------|\n156: | AR-027 | CodeInterpreterClient implementation provides the foundation for client patterns |\n157: | python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n158: | workload-manager/api.md | Control plane API specification |\n159: | router/api.md | Data plane API specification |\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Acceptance Criteria\n164: \n165: | ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n166: |----|-----------|---------------------|\n167: | AC-001 | AgentRuntimeClient constructs with default parameters | Unit test |\n168: | AC-002 | AgentRuntimeClient creates session when session_id not provided | Unit test with mock |\n169: | AC-003 | Context manager properly cleans up resources | Integration test |\n170: | AC-004 | Data plane init failure triggers session cleanup | Unit test with mock |\n171: | AC-005 | ValueError raised when router_url missing | Unit test |\n172: | AC-006 | execute_tool makes correct HTTP POST | Unit test with mock |\n173: | AC-007 | list_tools makes correct HTTP GET | Unit test with mock |\n174: | AC-008 | get_tool_schema makes correct HTTP GET | Unit test with mock |\n175: | AC-009 | File operations use correct endpoints and headers | Unit test with mock |\n176: | AC-010 | stop() closes all connections and deletes session | Unit test with mock |\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Test Strategy\n181: \n182: 1. **Unit Tests**: Test each method in isolation with mocked HTTP responses\n183: 2. **Integration Tests**: Test against mock server or test environment\n184: 3. **Error Handling Tests**: Verify proper exception handling for network errors, timeouts, and API errors\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Implementation Notes\n189: \n190: - Follow the same patterns established in AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient)\n191: - Use the existing `ControlPlaneClient` from AR-027 for session management\n192: - Leverage the utility modules (http, log, utils) created in AR-027\n193: - Maintain consistency with the exception hierarchy defined in AR-027\n\n(End of file - total 193 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Agent Runtime sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute tools/files via the Router (data plane).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-028\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient)\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nBuilding upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869162942,"end":1775869162962}}}}
