{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775869179760,"sessionID":"ses_285f34793ffedZA5DeT9533kBe","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0d376e001a4mmwyEpMoKjHx","messageID":"msg_d7a0d29c1001pQ3RVKbHQSOA4e","sessionID":"ses_285f34793ffedZA5DeT9533kBe","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775869185927,"sessionID":"ses_285f34793ffedZA5DeT9533kBe","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0d483c0016hVaRLBqq9g84X","messageID":"msg_d7a0d29c1001pQ3RVKbHQSOA4e","sessionID":"ses_285f34793ffedZA5DeT9533kBe","type":"text","text":"The existing AR-028 delta-spec.md has discrepancies with the base specs. According to the base design.md/spec.md, `AgentRuntimeClient` only has:\n- `__init__`, `__enter__`, `__exit__`, `invoke`, `close` methods\n- NOT `execute_tool`, `list_tools`, `get_tool_schema`, file operations\n\nIt's also missing key scenarios from the base spec:\n- Bootstrap session id\n- Invoke without session\n- Invoke timeout tuple\n\nLet me update the delta-spec.md to align with the base specifications:","time":{"start":1775869185925,"end":1775869185925}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869262720,"sessionID":"ses_285f34793ffedZA5DeT9533kBe","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0d4f880017A8VIoLDjZTY9P","messageID":"msg_d7a0d29c1001pQ3RVKbHQSOA4e","sessionID":"ses_285f34793ffedZA5DeT9533kBe","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_7e187bc18ac24808975176a2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","newString":"# Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to invoke Agent Runtime workloads through the Router (data plane) after bootstrapping a session.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-028\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient foundation)\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nBuilding upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Router (bootstrap session)\n2. Invoke tools via the Agent Runtime data plane with JSON payloads\n3. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-028-001: AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or bootstraps a new session via GET on the invocation endpoint, then initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()`, which closes the underlying `requests.Session`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-B — Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-C — Constructor parameters with defaults\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL set `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `verbose=False`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-002: Session bootstrapping\n\nThe system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-002-A — Bootstrap session id\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **AND** if the header is missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-002-B — Reuse existing session_id\n- **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-session-123\"` is provided to constructor\n- **WHEN** initialization runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL skip session bootstrapping and use the provided session_id directly\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-003: Invoke method\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` method that POSTs JSON payloads to the data plane with session header.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-A — Invoke without session\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy (None or empty)\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-B — Invoke with payload\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"tool\": \"calculator\", \"input\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}}, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL POST to `{base_url}` with JSON body `{\"tool\": \"calculator\", \"input\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}}`\n- **AND** headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **AND** return the response from the data plane\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-C — Invoke timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-D — Invoke with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=60)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `60` seconds\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-004: Data Plane Client URL Construction\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL construct the base URL from router components.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-A — Base URL from router components\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"https://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"prod\"`, `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without `base_url`\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` as `https://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-B — Explicit base URL\n- **GIVEN** `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"` is explicitly provided\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-005: Session Header\n\nAll data plane requests SHALL include the session ID header.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-005-A — Session header on requests\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"session-123\"`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: session-123`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-005-B — Session header constant\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n- **WHEN** inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL have class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-006: Close method\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `close` method to clean up resources.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-006-A — Close releases resources\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` has an active session\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed\n\n---\n\n## Non-Requirements\n\nThe following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n- Code interpretation functionality (covered in AR-027)\n- WebSocket connections for streaming (future enhancement)\n- Authentication beyond JWT token (handled by ControlPlaneClient)\n- Tool implementation (provided by runtime)\n- File operations directly on AgentRuntimeClient (different use case)\n- Tool discovery endpoints (list_tools, get_tool_schema) - not in base spec\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Description |\n|------------|-------------|\n| AR-027 | CodeInterpreterClient implementation provides the foundation for client patterns |\n| python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n| python-sdk/spec.md | Base specification with AgentRuntimeClient requirements |\n| router/api.md | Data plane API specification |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n|----|-----------|---------------------|\n| AC-001 | AgentRuntimeClient constructs with default parameters (agent_name, namespace, timeout, connect_timeout) | Unit test |\n| AC-002 | AgentRuntimeClient raises ValueError when router_url missing | Unit test |\n| AC-003 | Context manager properly closes resources | Integration test |\n| AC-004 | Bootstrap session id via GET reads x-agentcube-session-id header | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-005 | Missing session header during bootstrap raises ValueError | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-006 | Reusing provided session_id skips bootstrap | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-007 | invoke() raises ValueError when session_id is falsy | Unit test |\n| AC-008 | invoke() makes correct HTTP POST with JSON payload | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-009 | invoke() includes x-agentcube-session-id header | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-010 | invoke() uses timeout tuple (connect_timeout, self.timeout) when timeout=None | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-011 | invoke() uses custom timeout when provided | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-012 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components | Unit test |\n| AC-013 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient has SESSION_HEADER class constant | Unit test |\n| AC-014 | close() closes the requests.Session | Unit test with mock |\n\n---\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n1. **Unit Tests**: Test each method in isolation with mocked HTTP responses\n2. **Integration Tests**: Test against mock server or test environment\n3. **Error Handling Tests**: Verify proper exception handling for network errors, timeouts, and API errors\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Follow the same patterns established in AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient)\n- AgentRuntimeClient has simpler lifecycle than CodeInterpreterClient (no control plane session management)\n- The `invoke` method is the primary way to interact with Agent Runtime\n- Use the utility modules (http, log, utils) created in AR-027\n- Maintain consistency with the exception hierarchy defined in AR-027","oldString":"# Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Agent Runtime sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute tools/files via the Router (data plane).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-028\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient)\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nBuilding upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)\n2. Execute tools and manage files through the Router (data plane)\n3. Query available tools and their schemas\n4. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-028-001: AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-B — Data plane init failure after session create\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-C — Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-D — Constructor parameters with defaults\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL set `name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-002: Tool Execution\n\nThe system SHALL provide a method to execute tools via the data plane.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-002-A — Execute tool with parameters\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `execute_tool(tool_name=\"calculator\", parameters={\"expression\": \"2+2\"}, timeout=30)` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL POST to `{base_url}/api/execute` with JSON body `{\"tool_name\": \"calculator\", \"parameters\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}, \"timeout\": \"30s\"}`\n- **AND** return the result from the data plane\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-002-B — Execute tool timeout\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `execute_tool(tool_name=\"slow-tool\", parameters={}, timeout=5)` is called\n- **AND** the tool takes longer than 5 seconds\n- **THEN** the client SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with timeout information\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-003: Tool Discovery\n\nThe system SHALL provide methods to discover available tools and their schemas.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-A — List available tools\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `list_tools()` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/tools`\n- **AND** return a list of tool names\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-B — Get tool schema\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `get_tool_schema(tool_name=\"calculator\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/tools/calculator/schema`\n- **AND** return the tool's input/output schema\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-004: File Operations\n\nThe system SHALL provide file operation methods via the data plane.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-A — Upload file\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/tmp/data.csv\", remote_path=\"/data/input.csv\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL POST multipart form data to `{base_url}/api/files` with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **AND** the file SHALL be available at `/data/input.csv` in the runtime\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-B — Download file\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/output/result.csv\", local_path=\"/tmp/result.csv\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/files/output/result.csv` with `stream=True`\n- **AND** write the content to `/tmp/result.csv`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-C — List files\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `list_files(path=\"/data\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/files?path=/data`\n- **AND** return a list of files in that directory\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-005: Data Plane Client URL Construction\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL construct the base URL from router components.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-005-A — Base URL from router components\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"https://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"prod\"`, `cr_name=\"my-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without `base_url`\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` as `https://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-005-B — Explicit base URL\n- **GIVEN** `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"` is explicitly provided\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-006: Session Header\n\nAll data plane requests SHALL include the session ID header.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-006-A — Session header on requests\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"session-123\"`\n- **WHEN** any data plane method is called (e.g., `execute_tool`, `list_tools`)\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: session-123`\n\n---\n\n## Non-Requirements\n\nThe following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n- Code interpretation functionality (covered in AR-027)\n- WebSocket connections for streaming (future enhancement)\n- Authentication beyond JWT token (handled by ControlPlaneClient)\n- Tool implementation (provided by runtime)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Description |\n|------------|-------------|\n| AR-027 | CodeInterpreterClient implementation provides the foundation for client patterns |\n| python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n| workload-manager/api.md | Control plane API specification |\n| router/api.md | Data plane API specification |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n|----|-----------|---------------------|\n| AC-001 | AgentRuntimeClient constructs with default parameters | Unit test |\n| AC-002 | AgentRuntimeClient creates session when session_id not provided | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-003 | Context manager properly cleans up resources | Integration test |\n| AC-004 | Data plane init failure triggers session cleanup | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-005 | ValueError raised when router_url missing | Unit test |\n| AC-006 | execute_tool makes correct HTTP POST | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-007 | list_tools makes correct HTTP GET | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-008 | get_tool_schema makes correct HTTP GET | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-009 | File operations use correct endpoints and headers | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-010 | stop() closes all connections and deletes session | Unit test with mock |\n\n---\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n1. **Unit Tests**: Test each method in isolation with mocked HTTP responses\n2. **Integration Tests**: Test against mock server or test environment\n3. **Error Handling Tests**: Verify proper exception handling for network errors, timeouts, and API errors\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Follow the same patterns established in AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient)\n- Use the existing `ControlPlaneClient` from AR-027 for session management\n- Leverage the utility modules (http, log, utils) created in AR-027\n- Maintain consistency with the exception hierarchy defined in AR-027"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md\n@@ -1,152 +1,149 @@\n # Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n \n ## Overview\n \n-This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Agent Runtime sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute tools/files via the Router (data plane).\n+This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to invoke Agent Runtime workloads through the Router (data plane) after bootstrapping a session.\n \n ## Base Specifications\n \n - **AR**: AR-028\n - **Module**: `sdk-python`\n - **Language**: Python\n - **Size**: M\n-- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient)\n+- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient foundation)\n \n ---\n \n ## Background\n \n Building upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n-1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)\n-2. Execute tools and manage files through the Router (data plane)\n-3. Query available tools and their schemas\n-4. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n+1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Router (bootstrap session)\n+2. Invoke tools via the Agent Runtime data plane with JSON payloads\n+3. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n \n ---\n \n ## Requirements\n \n ### AR-028-001: AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n \n-The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n+The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or bootstraps a new session via GET on the invocation endpoint, then initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`.\n \n #### Scenario: AR-028-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n-- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n+- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()`, which closes the underlying `requests.Session`\n \n-#### Scenario: AR-028-001-B — Data plane init failure after session create\n-- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n-- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n-\n-#### Scenario: AR-028-001-C — Router URL required\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-001-B — Router URL required\n - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n \n-#### Scenario: AR-028-001-D — Constructor parameters with defaults\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-001-C — Constructor parameters with defaults\n - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n-- **THEN** it SHALL set `name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n+- **THEN** it SHALL set `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `verbose=False`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n \n ---\n \n-### AR-028-002: Tool Execution\n+### AR-028-002: Session bootstrapping\n \n-The system SHALL provide a method to execute tools via the data plane.\n+The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL.\n \n-#### Scenario: AR-028-002-A — Execute tool with parameters\n-- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n-- **WHEN** `execute_tool(tool_name=\"calculator\", parameters={\"expression\": \"2+2\"}, timeout=30)` is called\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL POST to `{base_url}/api/execute` with JSON body `{\"tool_name\": \"calculator\", \"parameters\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}, \"timeout\": \"30s\"}`\n-- **AND** return the result from the data plane\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-002-A — Bootstrap session id\n+- **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n+- **WHEN** the client initializes\n+- **THEN** it SHALL `GET {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n+- **AND** if the header is missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n \n-#### Scenario: AR-028-002-B — Execute tool timeout\n-- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n-- **WHEN** `execute_tool(tool_name=\"slow-tool\", parameters={}, timeout=5)` is called\n-- **AND** the tool takes longer than 5 seconds\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with timeout information\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-002-B — Reuse existing session_id\n+- **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-session-123\"` is provided to constructor\n+- **WHEN** initialization runs\n+- **THEN** it SHALL skip session bootstrapping and use the provided session_id directly\n \n ---\n \n-### AR-028-003: Tool Discovery\n+### AR-028-003: Invoke method\n \n-The system SHALL provide methods to discover available tools and their schemas.\n+The system SHALL provide an `invoke` method that POSTs JSON payloads to the data plane with session header.\n \n-#### Scenario: AR-028-003-A — List available tools\n-- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n-- **WHEN** `list_tools()` is called\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/tools`\n-- **AND** return a list of tool names\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-003-A — Invoke without session\n+- **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy (None or empty)\n+- **WHEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` is called\n+- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n \n-#### Scenario: AR-028-003-B — Get tool schema\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-003-B — Invoke with payload\n - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n-- **WHEN** `get_tool_schema(tool_name=\"calculator\")` is called\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/tools/calculator/schema`\n-- **AND** return the tool's input/output schema\n+- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"tool\": \"calculator\", \"input\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}}, timeout=None)` is called\n+- **THEN** the client SHALL POST to `{base_url}` with JSON body `{\"tool\": \"calculator\", \"input\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}}`\n+- **AND** headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n+- **AND** return the response from the data plane\n \n----\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-003-C — Invoke timeout tuple\n+- **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)` is called\n+- **WHEN** the request is sent\n+- **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n \n-### AR-028-004: File Operations\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-003-D — Invoke with custom timeout\n+- **GIVEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=60)` is called\n+- **WHEN** the request is sent\n+- **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `60` seconds\n \n-The system SHALL provide file operation methods via the data plane.\n-\n-#### Scenario: AR-028-004-A — Upload file\n-- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n-- **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/tmp/data.csv\", remote_path=\"/data/input.csv\")` is called\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL POST multipart form data to `{base_url}/api/files` with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n-- **AND** the file SHALL be available at `/data/input.csv` in the runtime\n-\n-#### Scenario: AR-028-004-B — Download file\n-- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n-- **WHEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/output/result.csv\", local_path=\"/tmp/result.csv\")` is called\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/files/output/result.csv` with `stream=True`\n-- **AND** write the content to `/tmp/result.csv`\n-\n-#### Scenario: AR-028-004-C — List files\n-- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n-- **WHEN** `list_files(path=\"/data\")` is called\n-- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/files?path=/data`\n-- **AND** return a list of files in that directory\n-\n ---\n \n-### AR-028-005: Data Plane Client URL Construction\n+### AR-028-004: Data Plane Client URL Construction\n \n The `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL construct the base URL from router components.\n \n-#### Scenario: AR-028-005-A — Base URL from router components\n-- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"https://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"prod\"`, `cr_name=\"my-agent\"`\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-004-A — Base URL from router components\n+- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"https://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"prod\"`, `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`\n - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without `base_url`\n - **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` as `https://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n \n-#### Scenario: AR-028-005-B — Explicit base URL\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-004-B — Explicit base URL\n - **GIVEN** `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"` is explicitly provided\n - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated\n - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly\n \n ---\n \n-### AR-028-006: Session Header\n+### AR-028-005: Session Header\n \n All data plane requests SHALL include the session ID header.\n \n-#### Scenario: AR-028-006-A — Session header on requests\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-005-A — Session header on requests\n - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"session-123\"`\n-- **WHEN** any data plane method is called (e.g., `execute_tool`, `list_tools`)\n+- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n - **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: session-123`\n \n+#### Scenario: AR-028-005-B — Session header constant\n+- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n+- **WHEN** inspected\n+- **THEN** it SHALL have class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n+\n ---\n \n+### AR-028-006: Close method\n+\n+The system SHALL provide a `close` method to clean up resources.\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-028-006-A — Close releases resources\n+- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` has an active session\n+- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n+- **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed\n+\n+---\n+\n ## Non-Requirements\n \n The following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n - Code interpretation functionality (covered in AR-027)\n - WebSocket connections for streaming (future enhancement)\n - Authentication beyond JWT token (handled by ControlPlaneClient)\n - Tool implementation (provided by runtime)\n+- File operations directly on AgentRuntimeClient (different use case)\n+- Tool discovery endpoints (list_tools, get_tool_schema) - not in base spec\n \n ---\n \n ## Dependencies\n@@ -154,27 +151,31 @@\n | Dependency | Description |\n |------------|-------------|\n | AR-027 | CodeInterpreterClient implementation provides the foundation for client patterns |\n | python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n-| workload-manager/api.md | Control plane API specification |\n+| python-sdk/spec.md | Base specification with AgentRuntimeClient requirements |\n | router/api.md | Data plane API specification |\n \n ---\n \n ## Acceptance Criteria\n \n | ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n |----|-----------|---------------------|\n-| AC-001 | AgentRuntimeClient constructs with default parameters | Unit test |\n-| AC-002 | AgentRuntimeClient creates session when session_id not provided | Unit test with mock |\n-| AC-003 | Context manager properly cleans up resources | Integration test |\n-| AC-004 | Data plane init failure triggers session cleanup | Unit test with mock |\n-| AC-005 | ValueError raised when router_url missing | Unit test |\n-| AC-006 | execute_tool makes correct HTTP POST | Unit test with mock |\n-| AC-007 | list_tools makes correct HTTP GET | Unit test with mock |\n-| AC-008 | get_tool_schema makes correct HTTP GET | Unit test with mock |\n-| AC-009 | File operations use correct endpoints and headers | Unit test with mock |\n-| AC-010 | stop() closes all connections and deletes session | Unit test with mock |\n+| AC-001 | AgentRuntimeClient constructs with default parameters (agent_name, namespace, timeout, connect_timeout) | Unit test |\n+| AC-002 | AgentRuntimeClient raises ValueError when router_url missing | Unit test |\n+| AC-003 | Context manager properly closes resources | Integration test |\n+| AC-004 | Bootstrap session id via GET reads x-agentcube-session-id header | Unit test with mock |\n+| AC-005 | Missing session header during bootstrap raises ValueError | Unit test with mock |\n+| AC-006 | Reusing provided session_id skips bootstrap | Unit test with mock |\n+| AC-007 | invoke() raises ValueError when session_id is falsy | Unit test |\n+| AC-008 | invoke() makes correct HTTP POST with JSON payload | Unit test with mock |\n+| AC-009 | invoke() includes x-agentcube-session-id header | Unit test with mock |\n+| AC-010 | invoke() uses timeout tuple (connect_timeout, self.timeout) when timeout=None | Unit test with mock |\n+| AC-011 | invoke() uses custom timeout when provided | Unit test with mock |\n+| AC-012 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components | Unit test |\n+| AC-013 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient has SESSION_HEADER class constant | Unit test |\n+| AC-014 | close() closes the requests.Session | Unit test with mock |\n \n ---\n \n ## Test Strategy\n@@ -187,7 +188,8 @@\n \n ## Implementation Notes\n \n - Follow the same patterns established in AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient)\n-- Use the existing `ControlPlaneClient` from AR-027 for session management\n-- Leverage the utility modules (http, log, utils) created in AR-027\n+- AgentRuntimeClient has simpler lifecycle than CodeInterpreterClient (no control plane session management)\n+- The `invoke` method is the primary way to interact with Agent Runtime\n+- Use the utility modules (http, log, utils) created in AR-027\n - Maintain consistency with the exception hierarchy defined in AR-027\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Agent Runtime sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute tools/files via the Router (data plane).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-028\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient)\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nBuilding upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)\n2. Execute tools and manage files through the Router (data plane)\n3. Query available tools and their schemas\n4. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-028-001: AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-B — Data plane init failure after session create\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-C — Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-D — Constructor parameters with defaults\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL set `name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-002: Tool Execution\n\nThe system SHALL provide a method to execute tools via the data plane.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-002-A — Execute tool with parameters\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `execute_tool(tool_name=\"calculator\", parameters={\"expression\": \"2+2\"}, timeout=30)` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL POST to `{base_url}/api/execute` with JSON body `{\"tool_name\": \"calculator\", \"parameters\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}, \"timeout\": \"30s\"}`\n- **AND** return the result from the data plane\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-002-B — Execute tool timeout\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `execute_tool(tool_name=\"slow-tool\", parameters={}, timeout=5)` is called\n- **AND** the tool takes longer than 5 seconds\n- **THEN** the client SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with timeout information\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-003: Tool Discovery\n\nThe system SHALL provide methods to discover available tools and their schemas.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-A — List available tools\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `list_tools()` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/tools`\n- **AND** return a list of tool names\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-B — Get tool schema\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `get_tool_schema(tool_name=\"calculator\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/tools/calculator/schema`\n- **AND** return the tool's input/output schema\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-004: File Operations\n\nThe system SHALL provide file operation methods via the data plane.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-A — Upload file\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/tmp/data.csv\", remote_path=\"/data/input.csv\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL POST multipart form data to `{base_url}/api/files` with `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **AND** the file SHALL be available at `/data/input.csv` in the runtime\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-B — Download file\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/output/result.csv\", local_path=\"/tmp/result.csv\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/files/output/result.csv` with `stream=True`\n- **AND** write the content to `/tmp/result.csv`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-C — List files\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `list_files(path=\"/data\")` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL GET `{base_url}/api/files?path=/data`\n- **AND** return a list of files in that directory\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-005: Data Plane Client URL Construction\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL construct the base URL from router components.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-005-A — Base URL from router components\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"https://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"prod\"`, `cr_name=\"my-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without `base_url`\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` as `https://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-005-B — Explicit base URL\n- **GIVEN** `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"` is explicitly provided\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-006: Session Header\n\nAll data plane requests SHALL include the session ID header.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-006-A — Session header on requests\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"session-123\"`\n- **WHEN** any data plane method is called (e.g., `execute_tool`, `list_tools`)\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: session-123`\n\n---\n\n## Non-Requirements\n\nThe following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n- Code interpretation functionality (covered in AR-027)\n- WebSocket connections for streaming (future enhancement)\n- Authentication beyond JWT token (handled by ControlPlaneClient)\n- Tool implementation (provided by runtime)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Description |\n|------------|-------------|\n| AR-027 | CodeInterpreterClient implementation provides the foundation for client patterns |\n| python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n| workload-manager/api.md | Control plane API specification |\n| router/api.md | Data plane API specification |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n|----|-----------|---------------------|\n| AC-001 | AgentRuntimeClient constructs with default parameters | Unit test |\n| AC-002 | AgentRuntimeClient creates session when session_id not provided | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-003 | Context manager properly cleans up resources | Integration test |\n| AC-004 | Data plane init failure triggers session cleanup | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-005 | ValueError raised when router_url missing | Unit test |\n| AC-006 | execute_tool makes correct HTTP POST | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-007 | list_tools makes correct HTTP GET | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-008 | get_tool_schema makes correct HTTP GET | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-009 | File operations use correct endpoints and headers | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-010 | stop() closes all connections and deletes session | Unit test with mock |\n\n---\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n1. **Unit Tests**: Test each method in isolation with mocked HTTP responses\n2. **Integration Tests**: Test against mock server or test environment\n3. **Error Handling Tests**: Verify proper exception handling for network errors, timeouts, and API errors\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Follow the same patterns established in AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient)\n- Use the existing `ControlPlaneClient` from AR-027 for session management\n- Leverage the utility modules (http, log, utils) created in AR-027\n- Maintain consistency with the exception hierarchy defined in AR-027","after":"# Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to invoke Agent Runtime workloads through the Router (data plane) after bootstrapping a session.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-028\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient foundation)\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nBuilding upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Router (bootstrap session)\n2. Invoke tools via the Agent Runtime data plane with JSON payloads\n3. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-028-001: AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or bootstraps a new session via GET on the invocation endpoint, then initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()`, which closes the underlying `requests.Session`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-B — Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-001-C — Constructor parameters with defaults\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL set `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `verbose=False`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-002: Session bootstrapping\n\nThe system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-002-A — Bootstrap session id\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **AND** if the header is missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-002-B — Reuse existing session_id\n- **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-session-123\"` is provided to constructor\n- **WHEN** initialization runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL skip session bootstrapping and use the provided session_id directly\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-003: Invoke method\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` method that POSTs JSON payloads to the data plane with session header.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-A — Invoke without session\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy (None or empty)\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-B — Invoke with payload\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"tool\": \"calculator\", \"input\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}}, timeout=None)` is called\n- **THEN** the client SHALL POST to `{base_url}` with JSON body `{\"tool\": \"calculator\", \"input\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}}`\n- **AND** headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **AND** return the response from the data plane\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-C — Invoke timeout tuple\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-003-D — Invoke with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=60)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `60` seconds\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-004: Data Plane Client URL Construction\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL construct the base URL from router components.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-A — Base URL from router components\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"https://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"prod\"`, `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without `base_url`\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` as `https://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-004-B — Explicit base URL\n- **GIVEN** `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"` is explicitly provided\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-005: Session Header\n\nAll data plane requests SHALL include the session ID header.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-005-A — Session header on requests\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"session-123\"`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: session-123`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-005-B — Session header constant\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n- **WHEN** inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL have class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n---\n\n### AR-028-006: Close method\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `close` method to clean up resources.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-028-006-A — Close releases resources\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` has an active session\n- **WHEN** `close()` is called\n- **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed\n\n---\n\n## Non-Requirements\n\nThe following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n- Code interpretation functionality (covered in AR-027)\n- WebSocket connections for streaming (future enhancement)\n- Authentication beyond JWT token (handled by ControlPlaneClient)\n- Tool implementation (provided by runtime)\n- File operations directly on AgentRuntimeClient (different use case)\n- Tool discovery endpoints (list_tools, get_tool_schema) - not in base spec\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Description |\n|------------|-------------|\n| AR-027 | CodeInterpreterClient implementation provides the foundation for client patterns |\n| python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n| python-sdk/spec.md | Base specification with AgentRuntimeClient requirements |\n| router/api.md | Data plane API specification |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n|----|-----------|---------------------|\n| AC-001 | AgentRuntimeClient constructs with default parameters (agent_name, namespace, timeout, connect_timeout) | Unit test |\n| AC-002 | AgentRuntimeClient raises ValueError when router_url missing | Unit test |\n| AC-003 | Context manager properly closes resources | Integration test |\n| AC-004 | Bootstrap session id via GET reads x-agentcube-session-id header | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-005 | Missing session header during bootstrap raises ValueError | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-006 | Reusing provided session_id skips bootstrap | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-007 | invoke() raises ValueError when session_id is falsy | Unit test |\n| AC-008 | invoke() makes correct HTTP POST with JSON payload | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-009 | invoke() includes x-agentcube-session-id header | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-010 | invoke() uses timeout tuple (connect_timeout, self.timeout) when timeout=None | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-011 | invoke() uses custom timeout when provided | Unit test with mock |\n| AC-012 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components | Unit test |\n| AC-013 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient has SESSION_HEADER class constant | Unit test |\n| AC-014 | close() closes the requests.Session | Unit test with mock |\n\n---\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n1. **Unit Tests**: Test each method in isolation with mocked HTTP responses\n2. **Integration Tests**: Test against mock server or test environment\n3. **Error Handling Tests**: Verify proper exception handling for network errors, timeouts, and API errors\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Follow the same patterns established in AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient)\n- AgentRuntimeClient has simpler lifecycle than CodeInterpreterClient (no control plane session management)\n- The `invoke` method is the primary way to interact with Agent Runtime\n- Use the utility modules (http, log, utils) created in AR-027\n- Maintain consistency with the exception hierarchy defined in AR-027","additions":83,"deletions":81},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869262643,"end":1775869262714}}}}
